<br>
When I first started playing Daoc my mind seemed to think this was still EQ and I got all pissed because I couldn't set up the controls exactly the same.  Obviously after a while that stopped but my initial reaction was wow, just like EQ.  I felt nothing like that going from UO to EQ, however, because those two really are games that don't hold much comparision.<br>
<br>
Mythic adopted a lot of things from EQ.  Thats not bad, thats almost expected considering how succesful EQ is/was.  It also opens up means of comparision because obviously they aren't the same game.<br>
<br>
If they weren't so similar and such a threat to each other, we wouldn't be seeing all these drastic changes in EQ and Mythic would feel no rush to add content/quests and fix stuff.  Lets be glad for comparisions.<br>
